The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Saturday, May 08, 2004 				 Kabi Pranam
																								Rabindranath Tagore is synonymous with the culture and literary heritage of Bengal. To commemorate his 143rd birth anniversary, a number of programmes are being held today in different parts of the city. As in previous years, the cultural department of the Government of West Bengal has organised a programme of dance, music and recitation at Rabindra Sadan campus. Beginning at the crack of dawn at 5.30. A similar function takes place simultaneously at Jorasanko Thakurbari. Visva Bharati presents a concert of Tagores literary masterpeices at Kala Mandir, 9 am. The West Bengal Dance Group Federation hosts Phirey Cholo Maatir Taney, a programme of dances choreographed to popular Tagore songs, performed by 30 dance troupes at Madhusudan Mancha, 6 pm. Sri Aurobindo Institute of Culture, Regent Park, hosts an evening of Rabindrasangeet by popular singers at 5.30 pm. Homage will be paid to Tagore through a recital of his songs and poems by Shrutiparishad and Srinandana at Salt Lakes HA Block Auditorium, 6.30 am. Among the Rabindra Jayanti celebrations to be held by the citys schools, Nava Nalandas concert in the morning, featuring eminent singers, deserves special mention.
